HEADWORD: Bottine
<hw>Bot*tine"</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. See
<er>Boot</er> (for the foot.).]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>A small boot; a lady's boot.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An appliance resembling a small boot furnished with
straps, buckles, etc., used to correct or prevent distortions in the
lower extremities of children.</def> <rj><au>Dunglison.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bottle</ent>⟦br⟧
